{
  "texts": [
    "Figure 15 illustrates the categories of DL methods used for point cloud compression tasks.",
    "Furthermore, voxel methods based on encoding domain use denser point clouds compared to point methods, while methods that require prior information are divided into unstructured and LiDAR sensor data utilization.",
    "Geometry-based methodsGeometry-based methods for point cloud compression can be categorized into lossy and lossless approaches.",
    "Lossy methods utilize CNNs based on autoencoders architecture for transforming the point cloud into a latent space of a lower dimension and then reconstructing an output similar to the input, treating the point cloud as a binary signal on a voxels grid [211,212].",
    "The decoding process is considered a problem of binary classification in a voxel grid, even though point clouds are sparse, resulting in class imbalance [213]."
  ]
}